── KEY FINDINGS ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  1. Peak 5h utilization (sliding vs tumbling):
     Feb: sliding 76.7%, tumbling 57.4%
     Mar: sliding 140.9%, tumbling 123.9%
     Apr: sliding 195.7%, tumbling 156.1%
     Sliding catches spikes that straddle tumbling boundaries.

  2. Under the old regime (0x cache_read), NO 5-hour window in any month
     exceeds the budget. Max quota(0x) across all sliding windows:
     21.8M = 12.1% of budget

  3. Under the new regime (1x cache_read), multiple sliding windows
     per day exceed the budget because cache_read tokens dominate.
